# Sell Premium on Every New Long Entry

Whenever a new long stock position is opened (any strategy, any script), the system
MUST immediately attempt to write a covered call against it.

This is the "wheel strategy" discipline: never hold uncovered long shares when
premium can be collected.

## The Rule

> **After every successful long stock BUY, call `write_covered_call()` from
> `post_entry_premium.py` before returning from the executor function.**

## Required Pattern

```python
from post_entry_premium import write_covered_call

# After confirmed long entry:
if entry_successful and shares_filled >= 100:
    cc_result = write_covered_call(ib, symbol=sym, shares_held=shares_filled)
    if cc_result["status"] == "executed":
        logger.info("CC written post-entry: %s $%.2f x%d  premium=$%.0f",
                    sym, cc_result["strike"], cc_result["qty"], cc_result["premium_total"])
    else:
        logger.info("CC skipped post-entry (%s): %s", sym, cc_result["reason"])
```

## What `write_covered_call()` Does

1. Checks `shares_held // 100` for available contracts
2. Finds nearest expiry within **21–45 DTE** (target 35)
3. Checks dividend calendar — skips if ex-date conflicts
4. Selects strike via delta selector (~0.20 delta) or 10% OTM fallback
5. Prices the mid via IB live/delayed data
6. Skips if mid < $0.10 (not worth commission)
7. Places a **GTC limit STO** at the mid price

## Applies To

- `execute_mean_reversion.py` — after every confirmed long fill
- `execute_dual_mode.py` — after every confirmed long fill
- `spotlight_monitor.py` — after every confirmed spotlight entry
- Any future entry script

## Exceptions (do NOT write a CC when)

- Shares held < 100 (can't write a contract)
- Symbol has ex-dividend date within the option window that exceeds 70% of premium
- Nearest OTM strike is < 5% OTM (too tight, cap upside too aggressively)
- Premium mid < $0.10 (not worth the commission)
- Leveraged ETFs (3x) held < 5 days — these are short-term momentum plays;
  write CCs only if held > 5 days with a flat/consolidating chart

## Logging

All CC results (executed or skipped) must be logged at INFO level.
Executed orders are also logged to `logs/post_entry_cc_log.jsonl`.
